    "2026-06-30 V1b — String/number/path literals (paired with V1b-T): fills src/lexer/lexer.ts string + number scanning and the src/lexer/literals.ts seam. The string scanner decodes the escape table (\\\" \\' \\ \\n \\t \\r \\u{XXXX}) into Token.value (Token.text keeps the verbatim source slice), firing loom/parse/illegal-escape (message \"illegal escape sequence: \\<char>\") for an unrecognised escape (including a dangling backslash at EOL/EOF) and loom/parse/invalid-unicode-escape (\"invalid Unicode escape: value is not a Unicode scalar value\") for a \\u{...} whose 1–6-hex-digit scalar exceeds U+10FFFF or lies in the D800–DFFF surrogate range (a well-formed scalar decodes via String.fromCodePoint). The number scanner sets Token.numericType (integer when there is no fractional or exponent part, else number), fires loom/parse/integer-literal-out-of-range (\"integer literal exceeds the safe-integer range\") when an integer literal's per-token magnitude exceeds 2^53-1 and loom/parse/number-literal-not-finite (\"number literal is not a finite IEEE-754 double\") when a number literal parses to a non-finite double (e.g. 1e400 → Infinity), and treats any digit/letter/underscore abutting the decimal literal — the loom 1.0-deferred 0x/0o/0b radix prefixes and the 1_000 underscore separator — as loom/parse/unsupported-feature (consuming the malformed run). literals.ts validatePathLiteral fires loom/parse/invalid-path-separator (\"invalid path separator: backslash in path literal\", located at the literal span) for any backslash, then the byte-exact lowercase final-segment check on the literal as written: an import path not ending in .warp → loom/parse/import-non-warp-extension, an invoke/tools path not ending in .loom → loom/parse/invoke-non-loom-extension, so .LOOM/.WARP is rejected identically cross-OS. checkIntegerNarrowing returns loom/parse/integer-narrowing (\"cannot narrow number to integer\") for a number value reaching an integer position and undefined for the one-way integer→number widening. Messages anchored to code-registry-parse.md per the Diagnostic message anchors rule; all functions pure (no module-level state, no broad catch, no ambient primitive, no Promise combinator or Sync call). All 15 V1b-T tests green; full suite 202 green, typecheck + lint clean.",
    "2026-06-30 V1b-T — String/number/path-literal tests (paired V1b impl): the src/lexer/literals.ts seam (validatePathLiteral / checkIntegerNarrowing inert stubs; NumericLiteralType / PathLiteralKind / PathLiteral / NarrowingSite shapes) plus two optional Token fields (value for the decoded string literal, numericType for the integer/number tag), and tests/literals-and-paths.test.ts with 15 failing tests. String and number behaviours are lexer-surfaced, asserted through lexLoom and the V7d producer-facing diagnostic seam (recording channel double capturing the batched loom-system-note details.diagnostics): the LEX code-keyed area — \\u{1F600} decodes to Token.value, and the simple escape table (\\n \\t \\\" \\) decodes to its characters; loom/parse/illegal-escape (\\x), loom/parse/invalid-unicode-escape (a value above U+10FFFF and a D800 surrogate), loom/parse/integer-literal-out-of-range (12345678901234567890 > 2^53-1, judged per-token), loom/parse/number-literal-not-finite (1e400 overflowing to Infinity), and loom/parse/unsupported-feature (0xFF / 0o17 / 0b101 / 1_000) all fire; 3.14/42 classify as number/integer on Token.numericType. The path-literal and narrowing rules need a parse/type context the tokeniser lacks, so they use the standalone literals.ts seams: loom/parse/invalid-path-separator (a backslash separator, located at the offending span), the byte-exact lowercase .LOOM rejection via loom/parse/invoke-non-loom-extension (cross-OS), and loom/parse/integer-narrowing (number→integer fires \"cannot narrow number to integer\", integer→number widening returns undefined). Messages anchored to code-registry-parse.md per the Diagnostic message anchors rule. Typecheck + lint clean; the 15 tests red on their own primary assertions (a missing decoded value, a missing numeric type, or an absent diagnostic) because the V1b escape-decoder / number-range checks / path validator / narrowing check are absent — fail-red-for-the-intended-reason; the other 187 tests stay green.",
    "2026-06-30 V1a — Lexer core (paired with V1a-T): implements src/lexer/lexer.ts. lexLoom UTF-8-validates the raw pre-normalisation bytes via firstInvalidUtf8Offset (a hand-written UTF-8 state machine returning the zero-based offset of the first invalid byte, rejecting overlong/surrogate continuation ranges; a non-UTF-8 BOM faults on its leading byte → offset 0) and, on failure, emits loom/load/invalid-encoding (file-only, message \"invalid UTF-8 encoding at byte offset <offset>\" anchored to code-registry-load.md) through the V7d emitDiagnosticBatch producer seam, never a direct pi.sendMessage. On valid input it strips a leading UTF-8 BOM (EF BB BF), normalises \\r\\n and bare \\r → \\n before any span is recorded (so CRLF and LF sources tokenise byte-identically — observable, not an implementation detail), then scanTokens produces raw tokens (// and /// line comments consumed silently; /* */ → loom/parse/block-comment and aborts the scan; a backslash outside any literal → loom/parse/stray-backslash; single-line string literals with \\-escaped chars; decimal numbers; identifiers vs the reserved-keyword set; greedy two-char operators ==/!=/<=/>=/&&/||). collapseContinuations folds raw newline runs into significant stmt-sep tokens under the closed continuation-trigger rule (grammar.md §Newline continuation): a run is swallowed when bracket depth is open, the prior token is a trailing binary/ternary operator (or the binding =, per the spec's own worked example), or the next token is a leading binary/ternary operator — decided once per run, so one or more blank lines never break a continuation. contextualDiagnostics fires loom/parse/reserved-keyword-as-identifier, loom/parse/schema-case-mismatch, loom/parse/binding-case-mismatch at let / let mut / fn / schema / enum name positions and loom/parse/single-line-if for an if/for/while/fn header whose logical line carries no {. All 15 V1a-T tests green; full suite 187 green, typecheck + lint clean; H2a module-level-mutable + H3a ambient scans green (lookup Sets are function-local; TextDecoder/TextEncoder are not banned ambient primitives).",
    "2026-06-30 V1a-T — Lexer-core tests (paired V1a impl): a src/lexer/lexer.ts seam stub (lexLoom(source, deps) — inert no-op returning an empty token stream and no diagnostics; Token/TokenKind/LoomSource/LexResult shapes, including the significant stmt-sep token marking a real statement boundary) plus tests/lexer-core.test.ts with 15 failing tests. Every lexer-surfaced diagnostic is asserted to fire through the V7d producer-facing diagnostic-emission seam — a recording channel double captures the batched loom-system-note details.diagnostics the lexer delivers through emitDiagnosticBatch → pi.sendMessage, never a direct out-of-band pi.sendMessage. loom/load/invalid-encoding: a non-UTF-8 byte ([0x68,0x69,0xff]) fails load (result.ok=false) at zero-based byte offset 2, message \"invalid UTF-8 encoding at byte offset 2\" anchored to code-registry-load.md, delivered as a batched loom-system-note (customType=loom-system-note, details.diagnostics present). lexical.md §Newline normalisation: LF and CRLF inputs tokenise to identical (non-empty) token streams. loom/parse/reserved-keyword-as-identifier (let match = 1), loom/parse/schema-case-mismatch (schema animal = …), loom/parse/binding-case-mismatch (let Foo = 1), loom/parse/block-comment (/* … */), loom/parse/single-line-if (if (x) stmt), loom/parse/stray-backslash (lone backslash) — each fires with its registry-anchored Message from code-registry-parse.md. grammar.md §Newline continuation: each of the four closed continuation triggers (unmatched open bracket, trailing binary/ternary operator, trailing comma inside an open bracket, leading binary/ternary operator) tokenises its spanning lines as one statement (statementGroups length 1), and one or more intervening blank lines do not break the continuation for both the trailing-trigger (let x =\\n\\n  foo) and leading-operator (let x = a\\n\\n  + b) forms. Typecheck + lint clean; the 15 tests red on their primary assertions (empty token stream, wrong statement count, no delivered diagnostic) because the V1a tokeniser/validator/continuation engine is absent — fail-red-for-the-intended-reason; the other 172 tests stay green.",
    "2026-06-30 V8b — FileSystem seam (paired with V8b-T): implements the PiFileSystem production adapter (src/seams/pi-file-system.ts) and the in-memory FakeFileSystem (tests/helpers/fake-file-system.ts) against PIC-13. PiFileSystem delegates to Node fs.promises / os — readText (utf8), readBytes (raw Buffer copied into a standalone Uint8Array preserving invalid UTF-8 per lexical.md §Encoding), writeText, exists (resolves false only on ENOENT through a Promise rejection handler rather than a broad catch — Node fs errors carry no narrow subtype — and rejects every other .code), homedir() via os.homedir() (no process.env, no platform branch), cwd() captured once at construction from process.cwd() carrying the `// allow-ambient: process.cwd — FileSystem` exempt-site comment the H3a scan admits, readdir (entry names only, no Unicode normalisation), lstat (does not follow symlinks), and realpath via promisified fs.realpath.native (full-path canonicalisation satisfying PIC-13's case-canonicalisation and byte-stable canonical-output guarantees that bare fs.promises.realpath does not). FakeFileSystem reports its constructor-injected homedir/cwd/files/dirs/symlinks/errors/caseInsensitive maps with the same Node-style .code rejection mapping (ENOENT/EACCES/EPERM), transitive symlink resolution with ELOOP cycle detection, ENOENT on a missing component, and case-insensitive realpath canonicalisation; writeText round-trips through readText. All 31 V8b-T tests green; full suite 172 green, typecheck + lint clean; the H3a ambient-primitive scan stays green (the single process.cwd() reference is allow-ambient-exempt).",
    "2026-06-30 V8b-T — FileSystem seam tests (paired V8b impl): a PiFileSystem production-adapter stub (src/seams/pi-file-system.ts, every member throws \"not implemented\") and an in-memory FakeFileSystem conforming-seam stub (tests/helpers/fake-file-system.ts, constructor takes homedir/cwd/files/dirs/symlinks/errors/caseInsensitive), plus tests/filesystem-seam.test.ts with 31 failing tests. PIC-13: the eight enumerated FileSystem members map Node .code values — readText/writeText/exists round-trip and reject ENOENT (false on exists) / EACCES / EPERM; homedir() and cwd() return constructor-injected values (Fake) and os.homedir() / a once-captured process.cwd() (Pi), never reading process.env / re-reading process.cwd(); readdir returns entry names only and preserves NFD bytes un-normalised (entry-name encoding guarantee); lstat does not follow symlinks; realpath follows symlinks transitively to a canonical absolute path, rejects ELOOP on a cycle / ENOENT on a missing component / EACCES / EPERM, and is byte-stable + case-canonicalising. lexical.md §Encoding: readBytes returns the raw pre-decode bytes as a Uint8Array preserving invalid UTF-8, carrying the same ENOENT/EACCES/EPERM .code mapping as readText. Typecheck + lint clean; the 31 tests red on their primary assertions because the V8b adapters are absent (fail-red-for-the-intended-reason); the H3a ambient scan and the other 141 tests stay green.",
    "2026-06-30 V7d — loom-system-note delivery channel: implements src/extension/system-note-channel.ts (paired with V7d-T). sendSystemNote sends one best-effort pi.sendMessage({customType:\"loom-system-note\", content, display, details}, {triggerTurn:false}) — never awaited, no .catch — and on a synchronous throw runs the fallback chain per runtime-event-channel.md §System notes: step 1 ctx.ui.notify(content,\"error\") (skipped when display:false or content:\"\", a throwing notify caught and swallowed), step 2 a loom/runtime/system-note-delivery-failed diagnostic (message=original note content, hint=underlying throw message), step 3 terminal console.error wrapped in try/catch (PIC-54: a console.error throw is silently swallowed and never propagates out of the chain, regardless of reach-path). The chain never aborts the slash handler or spawned subagent session. emitDiagnosticBatch is the producer-facing diagnostic-emission seam: it delivers a V7a-assembled Diagnostic[] as exactly one sendMessage per .loom (content=renderDiagnosticBatch(batch), details.diagnostics=full batch, no per-error fan-out) and re-emits on a re-scan with no dedup/supersede. createSystemNoteRenderer gains the PIC-21 render-time exception trap: an internal renderer-body throw (e.g. injected formatLines) does not escape — display:true returns a minimal Component rendering raw message.content, display:false returns undefined, and no loom/runtime/* diagnostic is emitted. Broad catches carry allow-broad-catch comments (pi-sdk-boundary for the pi.sendMessage / ctx.ui.notify SDK throws, PIC-21 for the renderer trap, PIC-54 for the diagnostic-step and terminal-console.error wraps). All 8 V7d-T tests green; full suite 141 green, typecheck + lint clean.",
    "2026-06-30 V7d-T — loom-system-note delivery-channel tests: the src/extension/system-note-channel.ts seam (sendSystemNote + emitDiagnosticBatch, inert no-op stubs; SystemNote/SystemNoteDetails/SystemNoteSender/UiNotifier/SystemNoteChannelDeps shapes; SYSTEM_NOTE_CHANNEL + SYSTEM_NOTE_DELIVERY_FAILED_CODE constants) plus an injectable formatLines seam added to createSystemNoteRenderer (so the PIC-21 test can drive an internal renderer-body throw without coupling to the dim-styling implementation), and tests/system-note-channel.test.ts with eight failing tests. Multi-error batch delivery: the V7a-assembled Diagnostic[] is delivered as exactly one sendMessage per .loom carrying the full batch serialised into content (renderDiagnosticBatch) and the Diagnostic[] in details.diagnostics, with no per-error fan-out (sent.length === 1 for a 3-diagnostic batch). Re-scan re-emits without dedup/supersede (two emitDiagnosticBatch calls => two sendMessage calls). PIC-21: an internal renderer throw does not escape the MessageRenderer invocation — display:true falls back to a minimal Component rendering raw message.content, display:false returns undefined, and no loom/runtime/* diagnostic is emitted (renderer takes no diagnostics sink by construction). loom/runtime/system-note-delivery-failed fallback chain: on a pi.sendMessage throw the runtime falls back in order — ctx.ui.notify(content,\"error\"), then a loom/runtime/system-note-delivery-failed diagnostic (message = original content, hint = underlying throw message), then a terminal console.error — skipping ctx.ui.notify when display:false or content:\"\", catching a throwing ctx.ui.notify and proceeding to the diagnostic step, and never aborting the handler; PIC-54: the terminal console.error is try/catch-wrapped at the definition site and a throw from it is silently swallowed without propagating out of the sendSystemNote fallback chain. Typecheck + lint clean; the 8 tests red on their primary behavioural assertions (delivery / fallback / PIC-21 hardening absent) — fail-red-for-the-intended-reason; other 133 tests stay green.",
    "2026-06-30 V7c — Placeholder rendering: implements the eight per-category renderers in src/diagnostics/placeholder.ts the V7c-T tests pin (DIAG-4). renderType (cat 1) re-serialises a Loom static type in source-grammar form (lowercase primitives, ` | `-joined unions with no parens, array<T>, Result<T, E>, inline object `{ f: T }` in declaration order). renderRuntimeValue (cat 2) stringifies per the canonical table — compact JSON.stringify for a schema-typed object (schema name does not surface), integer/number shortest-decimal with -0→0, Ok(…)/Err(…) for Result — with the category-2 string truncation: a string over 80 Unicode code points is cut to its first 77 code points + the literal \"...\" (counted by code point via Array.from, not UTF-16 units). renderConstruct (cat 3) emits the caller-supplied closed token-name (<construct>) or verbatim source span (<expr>). renderInteger (cat 4) is shortest-decimal with -0→\"0\". renderSourceDerived (cat 5) renders identifiers/paths bare, <key> double-quoted only when not identifier-shaped (^[A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*$), <char> raw when printable else \\xNN (≤U+00FF) / \\u{NNNN}, <descriptor> as <kind>:\"<value>\". renderUnderlyingError (cat 6) coerces a caught thrown value (object string .message; else String(v); else <unreadable> when String(v) throws) then first-line-truncates (\\r\\n and bare \\r → \\n, prefix up to first \\n, trailing whitespace preserved, <no message> when empty; \\u2028/\\u2029 ordinary). renderCategory7 (cat 7) dispatches the closed sub-rules (identifier/closed-enum verbatim, <uuid> canonical lowercase, numeric via cat 4, path/descriptor via cat 5). renderHostDerivedTail / renderHostIncompatible (cat 8) assemble the host-incompatible Message template `host incompatible (<kind>): observed <observed>, required <required>` with the host-derived <observed> first-line-truncated; the host version is passed in, never read from the ambient process (the src/** ambient-primitive ban). All 10 V7c-T tests green; full suite 133 green, typecheck + lint clean.",
    "2026-06-30 V7c-T — Placeholder-rendering tests: the src/diagnostics/placeholder.ts seam (eight per-category render functions — renderType (cat 1), renderRuntimeValue (cat 2), renderConstruct (cat 3), renderInteger (cat 4), renderSourceDerived (cat 5), renderUnderlyingError (cat 6), renderCategory7 (cat 7), renderHostDerivedTail/renderHostIncompatible (cat 8); inert stubs returning \"\") plus tests/placeholder-rendering.test.ts with ten failing tests pinning DIAG-4. Each of the eight categories asserts its normative vector byte-identically (array<integer | string> / Foo | null; compact JSON {\"name\":\"fluffy\"} + integer 42; arrow function + verbatim a + b span; -1/33/-0; bare identifier wibble + settings:\"~/work/looms\" descriptor + my-key→\"my-key\"/kind→kind; connection closed first-line + <no message>; closed-enum quit + uuid + integer; node-floor host tail). The category-2 80→81 code-point boundary: full at 80 code points, 77 chars + \"...\" at 81. The category-8 loom/load/host-incompatible (node-floor) row with the host version mocked to v18.19.0 (passed in, never read from process — the src/** ambient-primitive ban) asserts via the §8 anchored partial-match ^host incompatible \\(node-floor\\): observed (.*), required >=22\\.19\\.0$, sourcing the Message template from the registry (registryMessage) per the Diagnostic message anchors rule, never a full-Message equality (non-conformant for category-8 rows). Typecheck + lint clean; 10 tests red on their primary assertions (empty render '') because the renderer is absent — fail-red-for-the-intended-reason; other 123 tests stay green."
